snippet: The dispute in Westchester County, N.Y., involves a chief on medical leave, his temporary replacement and questions about missing cash and other evidence.
abstract: United States Attorney Preet Bharara says two-count complaint, for witness tampering and retaliation against a witness, has been brought against Joseph Krzeminski, police chief in Port Chester, NY; dispute that ensued after confrontation between Krzeminski and his temporary replacement John Telesca is complicated by federal inquiry into more than $26,000 in missing cash.
lead_paragraph: The dispute in Westchester County, N.Y., involves a chief on medical leave, his temporary replacement and questions about missing cash and other evidence.

headline.main: Federal Charges in Port Chester Police Dept. Feud
headline.print_headline: Federal Charges for Chief In Westchester Police Feud
